{
  "stem": "9590.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when he came back, there was a holiday meal.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The house looked very nice, different than every other day.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we felt good in that atmosphere.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a small town, about 2,000 people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Most of them were Jews.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The non-Jews lived in the outskirts of the-- of the city.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Jews lived amiable.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had a rabbi, and there were two temples.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Most people went, let's say, Saturday to the temple.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The older people went every day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I remember my grandfather going every day to shul and pray.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But my father went only on Saturday and on the holidays, and so did my mother, on the holidays.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The people lived pretty amiable with themselves.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I must say that I did not even feel that there is-- there are anti-Semites there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Maybe I was too naive and gullible not to see it, but that's my feeling.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We had organizations that provided for the poorer people, for the poorer Jews in our shtetl.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my mother, my father, always contributed generously whoever came and asked for the cause.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we were very Zionistic, my whole family.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My father and my mother dreamt of sometimes going to Israel, but their livelihood was there, and we did not-- they, rather, my parents, did not anticipate [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that something terrible can happen to them.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So they did not do much about it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a Jewish doctor, and there was a Gentile doctor.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The structure of the-- of the city was like-- like every little town.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It-- it had the beauty, the pulse.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The lifestyle was what the people made of it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "From day to day, most people struggled to make a living, and it was almost uneventful.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
